Operation<java.lang.Void>, SimulationEventHandler, TransMessageCallback
public class BTOperationSendStatistic<OwnerType extends DHTNode>
extends BTOperation<OwnerType,java.lang.Void>
implements TransMessageCallback

This operation sends periodically statistic data to the tracker. It reactivates itself every this.itsPeriod timesteps. Use the method stop to stop it. It is also responsible for requesting more peers from the tracker.

Author:
Jan Stolzenburg

operationTimeoutOccured

protected void operationTimeoutOccured()
Description copied from class: AbstractOperation
Each operation should have an operation timeout to ensure the proper functionality of the simulation. If a timeout event occurs in AbstractOperation.eventOccurred(SimulationEvent) this method is invoked to perform various actions. Default behavior is to break up the operation after the first timeout.
